WEBVTT

00:12.913 --> 00:14.381
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:14.414 --> 00:17.050
NAME'S DETECTIVE OUELLETTE.
25th PRECINCT.

00:17.084 --> 00:18.585
COME WORK FOR ME.
INTERNSHIP.

00:18.619 --> 00:19.653
FUCK, YEAH.

00:19.686 --> 00:22.189
WAIT, WHO ARE YOU?
I'M EMMA
FROM POUNCY HOUSE.

00:22.222 --> 00:23.056
WHAT?

00:23.090 --> 00:24.591
POUNCY HOUSE
PARTY RENTALS.

00:24.625 --> 00:27.661
WE'RE THE BIG BOY ON THE BLOCK
WITH A STICK.
IS THAT A THREAT?

00:27.694 --> 00:29.796
WHO'S THAT GUY?
Doug:
THAT'S KLEIN, THE C. E. O.

00:29.830 --> 00:32.866
WHOEVER TARGETED YOU
AS AN INFORMANT WAS
ASLEEP AT THE WHEEL.

00:32.900 --> 00:35.602
I'M SORRY ‐‐ YOU'RE
GONNA BE GOING BACK
TO THAT HALFWAY HOUSE.

00:35.636 --> 00:36.870
I'LL GO HIGHER ‐‐
C. E. O.

00:36.904 --> 00:38.038
YOU HAVE ACCESS
TO THE C. E. O.?

00:38.071 --> 00:39.940
I'M GLAD
YOU ASKED ME OUT.

00:39.973 --> 00:41.408
I DIDN'T ASK YOU OUT.

00:41.441 --> 00:42.943
OH, YES, YOU DID.

00:42.976 --> 00:43.944
QUESTIONS TO ASK HIM.

00:43.977 --> 00:45.445
GUESS IT'S TOO LATE
TO BACK OUT.

00:45.479 --> 00:47.181
I'D SAY SO.

00:47.214 --> 00:48.849
NUMBER‐ONE SON
IS REALLY PUTTING A DAMPER

00:48.882 --> 00:50.684
ON MY LEGIT BIKE BIZ.

00:50.717 --> 00:54.254
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN BEING THE COVER ANYMORE.

00:54.288 --> 00:57.691
THAT IS
SOME REALLY HEALTHY BUD.

00:57.724 --> 00:58.892
Smells super‐potent.

00:58.926 --> 01:00.527
ZOYA:
Tell them who I am.

01:00.561 --> 01:01.595
NANCY: She's...

01:01.628 --> 01:02.696
THE LOVE OF HER LIFE,

01:02.729 --> 01:06.400
ALTHOUGH I ALMOST
HAD A REASON TO DOUBT THAT,

01:06.433 --> 01:08.402
SEEING THAT LITTLE KISS
DOWNSTAIRS.

01:08.435 --> 01:11.238
I‐I'M SORRY.
YOU MIGHT WANT TO GO AWAY.

01:11.271 --> 01:14.474
BECAUSE I DON'T LIKE YOU,
AND I HAVE A BAD HABIT

01:14.508 --> 01:17.377
OF LOSING THINGS I DON'T LIKE
IN FIRE.

01:35.896 --> 01:38.098
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

01:41.235 --> 01:42.002
[ BEEP ]

01:42.035 --> 01:43.370
[ SNORTS ]

01:43.403 --> 01:45.939
YOU GOING SOMEWHERE?

01:45.973 --> 01:48.675
YOU MIGHT WANT TO GET
SOME NEW BATTERIES

01:48.709 --> 01:50.277
FOR YOUR SMOKE DETECTOR.

01:50.310 --> 01:51.078
WHY?

01:51.111 --> 01:53.981
SO YOUR LESBIAN‐LOVER
PYRO LADY

01:54.014 --> 01:56.216
WON'T BURN ME UP?

01:56.250 --> 01:57.017
HUH?

01:57.050 --> 02:02.089
YOU REALLY RESCUED ME
LAST NIGHT.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.790
YOU WERE TRYING TO
GIVE ME THE SLIP.

02:03.824 --> 02:05.092
I WAS TRYING...
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:05.125 --> 02:06.593
YEAH.
...TO LET YOU SLEEP.

02:06.627 --> 02:11.632
I WAS TRYING TO THANK YOU,
AGAIN, FOR, UM...

02:11.665 --> 02:13.834
A LOVELY EVENING...

02:13.867 --> 02:14.801
[ BEEP ]

02:14.835 --> 02:16.637
...BY REWARDING YOU
WITH SLEEP,

02:16.670 --> 02:17.871
BUT YOU'RE NOT ASLEEP.

02:17.905 --> 02:19.540
MM.
YOU'RE AWAKE,

02:19.573 --> 02:23.610
AND THE S. E. C. IS
GOING TO INDICT YOU FOR FRAUD.

02:27.681 --> 02:29.116
WHAT IS THAT?

02:29.149 --> 02:31.985
IS THAT A ‐‐
A THEORY OF YOURS?

02:32.019 --> 02:33.020
[ SIGHS ]

02:33.053 --> 02:35.889
THE S. E. C. KNOWS YOUR ‐‐

02:35.923 --> 02:38.025
KNOWS YOUR FUND IS A SHAM,
A PONZI SCHEME.

02:38.058 --> 02:39.993
THEY'RE GONNA
COME AFTER YOU.

02:40.027 --> 02:41.995
[ BEEP ]

02:42.029 --> 02:43.897
I WORE A WIRE LAST NIGHT
ON OUR DATE.

02:43.931 --> 02:45.832
I TOOK IT OFF.
IT'S GONE NOW.

02:45.866 --> 02:48.602
YOU WORE A WIRE?

02:53.640 --> 02:54.942
WHERE IS IT?

02:54.975 --> 02:57.010
IT'S GONE.

02:59.012 --> 03:00.647
HOW MUCH TIME DO I HAVE?

03:00.681 --> 03:02.015
I ‐‐ UH...

03:02.049 --> 03:04.017
I DON'T KNOW.
WEEKS?

03:04.051 --> 03:06.286
WEEKS, MAYBE MONTHS.

03:07.621 --> 03:10.057
STILL, UM, LAST NIGHT

03:10.090 --> 03:12.759
AND THIS MORNING ‐‐
IT WASN'T BULLSHIT.

03:12.793 --> 03:14.194
I DIDN'T MEAN ‐‐

03:14.228 --> 03:17.731
I THINK IT'S TIME
FOR YOU TO LEAVE.

03:20.434 --> 03:23.270
UH, I WAS
TRYING TO LET YOU SLEEP.

03:23.303 --> 03:24.972
[ BEEP ]

03:25.005 --> 03:28.108
I'M THE NEW BOSS,
SO HALF IS MINE.

03:28.141 --> 03:29.877
GIVE ME THE MONEY.

03:29.910 --> 03:32.579
GET AWAY FROM ME.
I'M NOT ALLOWED.

03:32.613 --> 03:33.780
UH, WHO ARE YOU?

03:33.814 --> 03:35.616
Andy: UH...
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:35.649 --> 03:36.550
ANYBODY HAVE
A TOOTHPICK?

03:36.583 --> 03:39.119
I THINK I GOT A NERD
LODGED IN MY MOLAR.

03:40.153 --> 03:43.056
I DON'T NEED ALL OF IT.
JUST GIVE ME $700.

03:43.090 --> 03:46.260
ENOUGH TO BUY SOME CLOTHES,
SOUP, AND A BEAR.

03:46.293 --> 03:47.961
A BEAR?

03:47.995 --> 03:48.962
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
OW! YOU'RE HURTING ME.

03:48.996 --> 03:50.831
ANDY BOTWIN.

03:50.864 --> 03:51.965
NANCY:
Um, just a heads up.

03:51.999 --> 03:54.201
I THINK ZOYA MIGHT BE
ON HER WAY OVER THERE.

03:54.234 --> 03:55.936
OH, YOU THINK?
WHY DO WE NEED A BEAR?

03:55.969 --> 03:58.038
FOR PROTECTION.
OHH! MY FACE!

03:58.071 --> 04:00.040
See if you can keep her

04:00.073 --> 04:01.675
FROM DESTROYING THE PLACE
UNTIL I GET THERE.

04:01.708 --> 04:02.709
Yeah. Sure thing.

04:02.743 --> 04:04.645
SHE SEEMS SO SANE
AND ACCOUNTABLE.

04:04.678 --> 04:06.046
YOU KEEP IT
IN A CAGE.

04:06.079 --> 04:09.449
IT GUARDS THE DRUGS.
IT'S VERY INTIMIDATING.

04:09.483 --> 04:11.818
UH, WE HAVE A SAFE,
AND I STUDIED AIKIDO.

04:11.852 --> 04:13.120
HA!

04:13.153 --> 04:14.955
I DON'T THINK SO.
AAH!

04:14.988 --> 04:16.223
PLEASE STOP DOING THAT.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.392
JUST TRY TO KEEP HER
OUT OF THE BACK ROOM, OKAY?

04:18.425 --> 04:19.893
GIVE HER A TOASTER.
SHE CAN FIX TOASTERS.

04:19.927 --> 04:21.762
SHE LOVES...TOASTERS.

04:21.795 --> 04:22.829
No! Sorry, Nance.

04:22.863 --> 04:24.097
I'M ‐‐ I'M NOT
A PART OF THIS.

04:24.131 --> 04:26.967
IN CASE YOU FORGOT,
I RUN A LEGITIMATE OPERATION.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.468
She is not my problem.

04:28.502 --> 04:29.536
SHE WILL BE.

04:29.570 --> 04:31.171
[ GRUNTING ]

04:32.072 --> 04:33.173
So you're on your way?

04:33.207 --> 04:35.542
What does that mean?
10 minutes? 5 minutes?

04:35.576 --> 04:36.743
Nance?

04:39.012 --> 04:41.181
SEE YOU IN A FEW.
Nance? You ‐‐

04:46.053 --> 04:47.020
WHAT DID YOU DO?

04:47.054 --> 04:49.056
I'M MAJORING
IN CRIMINAL JUSTICE.

04:49.089 --> 04:50.924
KEEP TALKING.

04:50.958 --> 04:52.860
THE POLICE OFFERED ME
AN INTERNSHIP.

04:52.893 --> 04:55.162
OH, JESUS.

04:55.195 --> 04:56.463
I GET SCHOOL CREDIT,

04:56.496 --> 04:58.498
AND I WORK THREE DAYS A WEEK
AT A REAL PRECINCT.

04:58.532 --> 05:01.001
I GET IT, OKAY?
YOU WANT MY ATTENTION.

05:01.034 --> 05:03.036
YOU WANT TO BUILD ME
A BEDROOM?

05:03.070 --> 05:05.005
SEND ME
YOUR PUPPET REVIEWS?

05:05.038 --> 05:08.342
I GET IT. W‐WHAT DO YOU NEED?
I'M LISTENING.

05:08.375 --> 05:10.010
LET ME BE
MORE THAN YOUR BANK.

05:10.043 --> 05:12.212
YOU KEEP PARTNERING UP
WITH THE WRONG SON.

05:12.246 --> 05:14.014
I CAN BE
YOUR MAN ON THE INSIDE.

05:14.047 --> 05:15.949
THE COPS THINK
I'M ONE OF THEM.

05:15.983 --> 05:17.651
YOU WANT ZOYA
TO GO BACK TO PRISON?

05:17.684 --> 05:20.354
I KNOW A GUY IN NARCOTICS
WHO CAN PLANT EVIDENCE.

05:20.387 --> 05:22.723
THEY'RE GONNA BE
ON TO YOU EVENTUALLY.

05:22.756 --> 05:24.057
I'LL PROTECT YOU.

05:24.091 --> 05:27.027
BABE, THESE ARE COPS.
I'M A DRUG DEALER.

05:27.060 --> 05:28.896
YOU'RE A MURDERER.

05:28.929 --> 05:31.732
WE CAN'T ALL PLAY
ON THE SAME KICKBALL TEAM.

05:31.765 --> 05:33.033
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

05:33.066 --> 05:35.369
I CAN DO THIS.

05:35.402 --> 05:37.771
I HAVE TO GET THIS.
DON'T FUCK UP.

05:37.804 --> 05:39.306
Hello?
MISS BOTWIN.

05:39.339 --> 05:41.175
OH, HI.
I WAS MEANING TO CALL YOU.

05:41.208 --> 05:44.211
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO COME DOWN
TO OUR OFFICE THIS AFTERNOON.

05:44.244 --> 05:46.580
WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

05:46.613 --> 05:48.916
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
SHIT.

05:48.949 --> 05:50.050
I'm still on the line.

05:50.083 --> 05:53.120
OH, SORRY.
UM, I'M ON MY WAY, OKAY?

05:53.153 --> 05:55.222
BYE.

05:55.255 --> 05:59.226
PLEASE BE CAREFUL WITH THE...
RED PART.

06:00.727 --> 06:01.929
I'M GOING SHOPPING

06:01.962 --> 06:04.131
FOR SOME NECESSITIES
WITH MY NEW BIKE.

06:04.164 --> 06:05.799
LISTEN, SVETLANA.

06:05.832 --> 06:08.368
NOT YOUR BIKE,
NOT YOUR BUSINESS.

06:08.402 --> 06:11.038
THIS IS THE FRONT OF THE HOUSE.
YOU LIVE IN THE BACK.

06:11.071 --> 06:13.707
SEPARATE. NOT EQUAL.
NOT RELATED.

06:13.740 --> 06:15.909
YOUR BUSINESS
IS WITH NANCY.

06:15.943 --> 06:17.845
I DON'T MAKE
SUCH DISTINCTIONS.

06:17.878 --> 06:20.113
YOU'RE MY PARTNER TOO...
UNTIL YOU'RE NOT.

06:20.147 --> 06:22.149
AND THEN NANCY AND I WILL MOVE
TO BURLINGTON, VERMONT,

06:22.182 --> 06:25.953
AND OPEN A WORLD‐CLASS
HOTEL FOR DOGS.

06:25.986 --> 06:27.654
SO JUST BE PATIENT,
MOYA LYUBIMAYA.

06:27.688 --> 06:30.791
THAT'S THE DREAM, HUH?

06:30.824 --> 06:31.992
STUPID HUBCAP.

06:32.025 --> 06:35.662
COPENHAGEN WHEEL.
MIRACLE OF SCIENCE.

06:35.696 --> 06:36.797
BIKES ARE TOO HEAVY.

06:36.830 --> 06:38.332
YOU WANT TO MAKE
REAL PROFIT,

06:38.365 --> 06:40.901
WE NEED SMALLER ONES
FOR DWARVES AND CHILDREN.

06:40.934 --> 06:43.170
YES. DWARF BIKES.
OF COURSE.

06:43.837 --> 06:45.939
CAREFUL.
CAREFUL WITH THAT!

06:45.973 --> 06:48.408
HELP ME TAKE OFF
YOUR PLASTIC BITCH WHEEL!

06:48.442 --> 06:50.911
[ CLANGING ]

06:50.944 --> 06:52.346
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:52.379 --> 06:54.848
GO AHEAD. DO WHATEVER YOU WANT,
'CAUSE WE'RE PARTNERS, RIGHT?

06:54.882 --> 06:55.983
WE'RE IN THIS TOGETHER.

06:56.016 --> 06:57.818
FINALLY YOU'RE
BEGINNING TO UNDERSTAND.

06:57.851 --> 06:58.919
OF COURSE I DO.

06:58.952 --> 07:01.288
OF COURSE I DO.
FAMILY, PARTNERS.

07:01.321 --> 07:03.390
I'VE ALWAYS LOVED
VERMONT.

07:03.423 --> 07:07.561
AND DOGS ‐‐ OH, MY GOD!
LOVE DOGS.

07:07.594 --> 07:10.931
THE THREE OF US TOGETHER?
CAN'T MISS.

07:10.964 --> 07:13.033
NO.
WHAT?

07:13.066 --> 07:15.035
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
THAT'S NOT
WHAT YOU MEANT?

07:15.068 --> 07:16.036
NO.
NO?

07:16.069 --> 07:17.704
NO!
WOOF! WOOF!

07:17.738 --> 07:19.173
NO. NO, NO! NO!

07:23.410 --> 07:24.178
JESUS.

07:24.211 --> 07:26.713
CLOSE THE DOOR.
HAVE A SEAT.

07:26.747 --> 07:28.882
HOW DID YOU...

07:28.916 --> 07:30.951
HAVE A MESSAGE
FOR YOUR BOSS

07:30.984 --> 07:33.954
AT POUNCY BOUNCY LAND
CASTLE WHATEVER PLACE.

07:33.987 --> 07:35.355
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

07:35.389 --> 07:39.993
SO YOU CAN TELL HIM
TO GO FUCK HIMSELF.

07:40.027 --> 07:41.295
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:41.328 --> 07:43.697
THAT'S IT? THAT'S YOUR MESSAGE?
"GO FUCK YOURSELF"?

07:43.730 --> 07:44.698
YEAH.

07:44.731 --> 07:45.999
WHAT? YOU DON'T LIKE
MY MESSAGE?

07:46.033 --> 07:47.501
I MEAN, IT'S FINE.

07:49.036 --> 07:51.004
HOW ABOUT,

07:51.038 --> 07:52.506
"IF I EVER SEE
YOUR UGLY PISSANT DEALERS

07:52.539 --> 07:54.908
"LOITERING AROUND
OUR BIKE SHOP AGAIN,

07:54.942 --> 07:56.143
YOU'LL FUCKING REGRET IT"?

07:56.176 --> 07:59.513
AND THEN, LIKE,
UNDERLINE "REGRET IT."

08:00.714 --> 08:03.584
GOOD.
SAY IT JUST LIKE THAT.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.786
OR SOMETHING EL‐‐

08:05.819 --> 08:06.987
THAT'S FINE.

08:07.020 --> 08:08.388
YOU SURE?

08:08.422 --> 08:10.724
YOU HUNGRY?

08:10.757 --> 08:12.259
I COULD EAT.

08:15.562 --> 08:17.564
NOT COMING TO VERMONT!
YOU'RE NOT INVITED!

08:17.598 --> 08:20.968
WHY? IT'S A FREE COUNTRY.
I CAN GO ANYWHERE I WANT.

08:21.001 --> 08:22.870
THIS IS FOR ME AND NANCY.

08:22.903 --> 08:24.004
AND ANDY MAKES THREE!

08:24.037 --> 08:25.906
I GOT GREAT IDEAS. I DO.
FOR INSTANCE ‐‐

08:25.939 --> 08:27.341
WHOA!

08:27.374 --> 08:30.110
WHY LIMIT OURSELVES TO DOGS?
WE COULD TAKE CATS, TOO.

08:30.143 --> 08:33.447
WE'RE NOT ACCEPTING CATS.
THIS IS NOT A PLACE FOR CATS.

08:33.480 --> 08:34.882
WE'LL HOUSE DOGS!

08:34.915 --> 08:36.750
IS EVERYTHING OKAY
OUT HERE?

08:36.783 --> 08:38.285
BACK INSIDE.
BACK INSIDE.

08:39.553 --> 08:41.622
LISTEN TO THIS PITCH.
READY? GET READY.

08:41.655 --> 08:43.991
GET RID OF DOGS ENTIRELY.
ONLY TAKE CATS.

08:44.024 --> 08:46.059
SHUT YOUR FUCKING FACE.

08:46.093 --> 08:47.895
WE CALL IT "KAT KENNEL."
WE SPELL EACH WORD ‐‐

08:47.928 --> 08:49.997
WITH A "K."

08:50.030 --> 08:51.565
WE'LL NEVER SPELL "CAT"
WITH A "K!"

08:51.598 --> 08:53.233
BUT YOU'RE WARMING
TO THE CAT IDEA, THOUGH?

08:53.267 --> 08:55.936
YOU'RE JUST JEALOUS
BECAUSE WHAT NANCY AND I HAVE,

08:55.969 --> 08:58.839
YOU WILL NEVER HAVE WITH
ANYONE ‐‐ NOT MAN OR BEAST!

08:58.872 --> 09:03.243
YEAH. IS THAT WHY SHE
SPENT THE NIGHT AT HER
BOSS' PLACE LAST NIGHT?

09:04.144 --> 09:07.047
CATS! CATS! CATS!

09:09.183 --> 09:10.817
Shane: YO, LEITZKE.

09:10.851 --> 09:12.986
GOT TO UPDATE
YOUR COMPUTER.

09:13.020 --> 09:14.454
CAN YOU COME BACK?
I'M WORKING.

09:14.488 --> 09:16.890
I GOT FREE COPIES
OF MICROSOFT WORD.

09:16.924 --> 09:18.292
SWEET.

09:19.927 --> 09:22.429
CAN YOU JUST ‐‐
JUST WRITE DOWN YOUR PASSWORD?

09:22.462 --> 09:24.298
OH, WELL...

09:24.331 --> 09:28.635
It's, uh, "policeofficer,"
all lower case.

09:28.669 --> 09:30.938
GOT IT.

09:30.971 --> 09:33.407
JUST GIVE ME LIKE
10 MINUTES.

09:33.440 --> 09:35.008
I'M GONNA GO GRAB A COFFEE.
YOU WANT?

09:35.042 --> 09:37.010
YEAH, COOL.
LIKE, WITH MILK.

09:37.044 --> 09:40.180
COFFEE, MILK. ON IT.

09:48.055 --> 09:49.189
Andy: HEY!

09:49.223 --> 09:51.892
HI. THANKS FOR COMING
WHEN YOU SAID YOU WOULD.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.827
I'M FINE, BY THE WAY.

09:53.861 --> 09:55.796
JUST A MINOR, UH ‐‐
MINOR CONTUSION.

09:55.829 --> 09:57.097
WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR?

09:57.130 --> 09:58.398
THE WIRE THING.

09:58.432 --> 10:01.768
THE TRANSMITTER
THE S. E. C. MADE ME WEAR.

10:01.802 --> 10:04.505
CAN'T FIND IT.
NEED TO RETURN IT.

10:04.538 --> 10:05.672
WHERE'S ZOYA?

10:05.706 --> 10:06.673
GONE.

10:06.707 --> 10:09.510
RAN OFF INTO THE ETHER.

10:09.543 --> 10:10.577
GONE?

10:10.611 --> 10:11.879
MM‐HMM.

10:11.912 --> 10:14.114
I MIGHT HAVE, UH,
MENTIONED SOMETHING

10:14.147 --> 10:17.784
ABOUT YOUR SLUMBER PARTY
LAST NIGHT WITH YOUR BOSSY‐BOSS.

10:17.818 --> 10:18.785
GREAT.

10:18.819 --> 10:21.588
THE LAST GUY
WHO MADE HER JEALOUS,

10:21.622 --> 10:23.457
SHE BURNED IN HIS SLEEP.

10:23.490 --> 10:25.626
SHE BURNS PEOPLE?

10:25.659 --> 10:27.995
IT'S SORT OF HER THING.

10:28.028 --> 10:29.663
SHIT. WELL,
SHE'S ‐‐ SHE'S MAD.

10:29.696 --> 10:35.435
SHANE, HAVE YOU SEEN
A‐A‐A BLACK NINJA SPYBOX THING?

10:35.469 --> 10:37.871
YOU MEAN YOUR MOTOROLA
LOW‐FREQUENCY TRANSMITTER?

10:37.905 --> 10:39.506
YES.
NO.

10:39.540 --> 10:42.976
BUT I STOLE THIS
FROM THE POLICE DEPARTMENT.

10:43.010 --> 10:45.479
WELL, THAT WAS FAST.

10:45.512 --> 10:46.580
THAT'S YOUR COMPETITION.

10:46.613 --> 10:48.982
THE WAY THEY OPERATE,
WHO THEY ARE, WHAT THEY SELL.

10:49.016 --> 10:50.017
AND THEIR WEAK SPOTS.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.151
HOW'D YOU GET THAT?

10:51.185 --> 10:52.920
I WALKED IN
AND PRINTED IT OUT.

10:52.953 --> 10:54.621
HE'S GOOD.

10:54.655 --> 10:57.057
SO, DOES THIS MEAN
THEY'RE GONNA GET BUSTED?

10:57.090 --> 10:59.059
UH, MAYBE.
PROBABLY NOT ANYTIME SOON.

10:59.092 --> 11:02.296
BUT FOR NOW, YOU'RE AT
AN INSANE COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE.

11:04.264 --> 11:05.532
RIGHT?

11:05.566 --> 11:07.234
WELL, IT'S SOMETHING.

11:08.902 --> 11:10.204
IS THAT IT?

11:10.237 --> 11:11.605
YOUR TRANSMITTER,
OVER THERE,

11:11.638 --> 11:13.941
UNDERNEATH THE CLOTHES
YOU THREW OFF LAST NIGHT?

11:13.974 --> 11:17.244
WHILE YOU WERE
CHANGING INTO A HUSSY?

11:17.277 --> 11:20.247
[ SIGHS ] I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'D DO WITHOUT YOU.

11:20.280 --> 11:22.950
UM, ZOYA NEEDS TO GO,
NANCE.

11:22.983 --> 11:24.952
SHE'S A PLAGUE
ON BOTH OUR HOUSES.

11:24.985 --> 11:26.353
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

11:26.386 --> 11:27.487
HOW?

11:27.521 --> 11:30.057
I DON'T KNOW, BUT I TOLD YOU
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

11:31.091 --> 11:33.560
LOOK, SHANE.
YOUR MOM'S MAKING PROMISES.

11:35.395 --> 11:38.899
Foster: I GET IT.
YOU DIDN'T MEAN TO DO THIS.

11:38.932 --> 11:40.267
J‐JUST STOP TALKING.

11:40.300 --> 11:43.704
I WAS GONNA TELL YOU, YOU SHOULD
PROBABLY LEAVE TOWN NOW.

11:43.737 --> 11:45.038
YEAH?

11:45.072 --> 11:47.174
WELL, PLAN "A"
WAS LIVE AND PROSPER.

11:47.207 --> 11:50.210
PLAN "C" ‐‐ DISAPPEAR.

11:50.244 --> 11:51.879
I USED TO HAVE
A PLAN "C."

11:51.912 --> 11:55.949
THEN PLAN "C"
TURNED BACK INTO PLAN "A."

11:55.983 --> 11:59.119
BUCKETS OF CASH,
TROPICAL ISLAND.

12:00.220 --> 12:02.222
YOU WANT TO COME
WITH ME?

12:02.256 --> 12:04.324
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
OKAY.

12:04.358 --> 12:06.026
COME ON.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.328
I'M SERIOUS.

12:11.164 --> 12:13.200
I CAN'T JUST
PACK UP AND GO.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.536
I HAVE PEOPLE
WHO NEED THINGS.

12:15.569 --> 12:17.104
CHILD PEOPLE.

12:18.472 --> 12:22.943
YOU'RE A SECRETARY/DRUG DEALER
WITH TWO GROWN‐UP KIDS.

12:22.976 --> 12:24.244
COME ON.

12:25.345 --> 12:28.949
TRAIN'S LEAVING.
COME ON.

12:28.982 --> 12:31.485
YOU'RE TAKING A TRAIN
TO AN ISLAND?

12:31.518 --> 12:33.187
MUST BE A MAGIC ISLAND.

12:33.220 --> 12:33.987
IT IS.

12:34.021 --> 12:36.223
IT'S A MAGICAL ISLAND.

12:36.256 --> 12:39.927
WE SLEPT TOGETHER
ONE TIME.

12:39.960 --> 12:43.997
WE ATE SKINK.
I RUINED YOUR LIFE.

12:44.998 --> 12:46.967
WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH ME?

12:47.000 --> 12:50.637
I DON'T KNOW.

12:50.671 --> 12:53.040
I LIKE YOU.

12:54.808 --> 12:59.146
AND IT'S, UH...
LONELY OUT THERE.

12:59.179 --> 13:00.414
HMM?

13:00.447 --> 13:03.684
I DON'T HAVE A SWIMSUIT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:05.919 --> 13:08.021
OKAY.

13:08.055 --> 13:10.724
YOU NEED A TOWNHOUSE?

13:10.757 --> 13:11.725
WHAT?

13:11.758 --> 13:12.759
TOWNHOUSE.

13:12.793 --> 13:14.728
IT'S GONNA TAKE THE FEDS
FIVE YEARS

13:14.761 --> 13:16.063
TO FIGURE OUT THIS MESS.

13:16.096 --> 13:17.264
IT'S PAID FOR.

13:17.297 --> 13:20.334
IT'LL LOOK GOOD ON YOUR
CUSTODY BATTLE. TAKE IT.

13:23.437 --> 13:24.571
WHAT ISLAND?

13:24.605 --> 13:26.006
EXCUSE ME?

13:26.039 --> 13:28.509
WHAT'S THE NAME OF THE ISLAND
WHERE YOU'RE GONNA BE?

13:28.542 --> 13:30.043
[ LAUGHS ]

13:30.077 --> 13:31.578
COME ON.
GIVE ME A HINT.

13:31.612 --> 13:33.680
CAN'T TELL YOU THAT.

13:33.714 --> 13:35.148
IT'S, UH...
STARTS WITH A...

13:37.918 --> 13:40.554
"B."

13:40.587 --> 13:42.389
UM, UH, BERMUDA!

13:47.461 --> 13:50.163
[ SIGHS ] BARBADOS.

13:52.199 --> 13:54.968
SO, HOW LONG YOU BEEN
SELLING PARTY FAVORS?

13:55.002 --> 13:57.871
PLEASE, LET'S NOT TALK
ABOUT WORK. I'M SICK OF WORK.

13:57.905 --> 13:59.039
YOU DON'T LIKE YOUR JOB?

13:59.072 --> 14:01.542
LOW PAY. SKETCHY BOSS.

14:01.575 --> 14:03.877
NOW HE MAKES TRANCE MUSIC
ON HIS LAPTOP,

14:03.911 --> 14:06.380
AND HE'S AN ASS‐GRABBER.

14:06.413 --> 14:08.749
I'VE ACTUALLY
BEEN THINKING OF QUITTING.

14:08.782 --> 14:11.552
THEN COME DEAL FOR US.

14:11.585 --> 14:12.486
WOW.

14:12.519 --> 14:14.588
YOU REALLY THINK
I COULD BE A MALE MODEL?

14:14.621 --> 14:16.557
WE'LL PAY YOU BETTER.

14:16.590 --> 14:17.991
I DON'T DATE DEALERS.

14:18.025 --> 14:21.228
THAT CAME OUT OF NOWHERE.

14:21.261 --> 14:22.896
DID IT?

14:22.930 --> 14:24.965
LEGITIMATE JOB OFFER.

14:24.998 --> 14:27.100
I'M NOT A DEALER.

14:27.134 --> 14:28.368
I'M MANAGEMENT.

14:28.402 --> 14:30.904
I DON'T KNOW. YOU GUYS SEEM
REALLY BIG AND CORPORATE.

14:30.938 --> 14:33.907
I ‐‐ I WOULDN'T WANT TO
GET LOST IN THE SHUFFLE.

14:33.941 --> 14:35.943
JUST ME AND NANCY.

14:35.976 --> 14:37.277
WHO'S NANCY?

14:38.145 --> 14:40.480
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
MY MOM.

14:40.514 --> 14:42.482
[ Laughing ] YOU DON'T.

14:42.516 --> 14:45.052
YOU...

14:45.085 --> 14:47.588
YOU RUN THIS THING
WITH YOUR MOM?

14:47.621 --> 14:50.390
HA.
THAT'S ADORABLE.

14:50.424 --> 14:52.926
IT'S JUST
YOU AND YOUR MOM...

14:52.960 --> 14:54.995
NAMED NANCY.

14:55.028 --> 14:57.898
DON'T LAUGH.
SHE'S A...PROFESSIONAL.

14:57.931 --> 15:00.300
YOU GUYS
GROW YOUR OWN STUFF?

15:00.334 --> 15:01.435
NO.

15:01.468 --> 15:04.171
BUT OUR STRAINS ARE EXCLUSIVE.
I CREATED ONE MYSELF.

15:04.204 --> 15:05.506
HOT.

15:05.539 --> 15:07.174
WHAT'S IT CALLED?

15:08.342 --> 15:09.810
MILF.

15:09.843 --> 15:12.112
AS IN
"MOTHER I'D LIKE TO FUCK"?

15:13.046 --> 15:14.515
THIS JUST GOT WEIRD.

15:16.049 --> 15:20.020
COME ON. JOIN THE TEAM.
IT'LL BE FUN.

15:20.053 --> 15:22.689
ALL RIGHT.

15:22.723 --> 15:24.625
MAKE ME AN OFFER.

15:29.963 --> 15:31.798
LET'S RECAP, SHALL WE?

15:31.832 --> 15:33.700
YOUR DATE
WITH MR. BIG SHOT

15:33.734 --> 15:36.904
PRODUCES NOTHING BUT
A GAPING HOLE IN MY CHEST

15:36.937 --> 15:38.939
WHERE MY CAREER
USED TO BE!

15:38.972 --> 15:41.775
AND YOU TURN OUT TO BE
A NARCOTICS DEALER,

15:41.808 --> 15:45.145
THEREBY ASSASSINATING
YOUR CREDIBILITY AS
A FUTURE WITNESS.

15:45.179 --> 15:47.014
AND FOR THE EXTRA
TWO POINTS,

15:47.047 --> 15:50.150
YOUR PSYCHO LESBIAN
EX‐CON EX

15:50.184 --> 15:52.953
THREATENS TO BURN TO DEATH
THE KEY SUSPECT

15:52.986 --> 15:55.622
WHO HOLDS
THIS ENTIRE CASE TOGETHER!

15:55.656 --> 15:57.958
THERE'S A PAPER TRAIL.

15:57.991 --> 16:00.127
I CAN DIG.
LET ME DIG.

16:00.160 --> 16:03.096
DIG YOURSELF A HOLE
TO CHINA.

16:03.130 --> 16:05.866
YOU'RE GOING
BACK IN THE SYSTEM.

16:05.899 --> 16:08.001
YOU PROMISED ME
NO MORE HALFWAY HOUSE.

16:08.035 --> 16:09.002
FUCK HALFWAY HOUSE.

16:09.036 --> 16:11.371
I'M CALLING MY FRIENDS
AT THE D. E. A.

16:11.405 --> 16:14.408
SO GET YOURSELF A LAWYER.
A GOOD ONE.

16:16.076 --> 16:18.846
AND I'LL NEED
OUR EQUIPMENT BACK, PLEASE.

16:18.879 --> 16:20.714
I LOST IT.

16:20.747 --> 16:22.082
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU LOST IT?

16:22.115 --> 16:23.884
I LOOKED.
I COULDN'T FIND IT.

16:23.917 --> 16:25.352
WELL,
THAT'LL BE 90 BUCKS.

16:25.385 --> 16:26.887
YOU'RE SERIOUS?

16:26.920 --> 16:28.622
I'M NOT PAYING FOR IT.

16:28.655 --> 16:32.459
DO YOU HAVE, UM, CHANGE?

16:32.492 --> 16:33.627
HERE'S $100.

16:33.660 --> 16:35.963
I DO NOT.

16:35.996 --> 16:38.932
AND WHERE'S
THE UGLY SCARF?

16:38.966 --> 16:40.968
I FORGOT.
I LEFT IT AT HOME.

16:41.001 --> 16:42.002
OH, GREAT.

16:42.035 --> 16:44.271
JOLENE SPENT A YEAR
KNITTING THAT THING.

16:44.304 --> 16:45.072
I KNOW.

16:45.105 --> 16:47.074
PLEASE!
DON'T CALL THE D. E. A.!

16:47.107 --> 16:48.942
I'LL, UH ‐‐
I'LL ADD TO THE SCARF!

16:48.976 --> 16:50.077
I'LL ADD FRINGE! I ‐‐

16:50.110 --> 16:52.179
BRING HIM IN.

16:53.080 --> 16:54.848
[ DOOR OPENS ]

16:54.882 --> 16:56.683
I'M NOT TELLING
YOU PIGS SHIT.

16:56.717 --> 16:57.851
DOUG?

16:57.885 --> 17:00.320
NANCY.
THEY GOT YOU, TOO, HUH?

17:00.354 --> 17:02.789
HAVE A SEAT,
MR. WILSON.

17:02.823 --> 17:04.358
JESUS CHRIST.

17:04.391 --> 17:06.760
WE KNOW YOU BEEN COOKING
THE BOOKS FOR KLEIN'S FUND.

17:06.793 --> 17:08.061
SO ONE OF YOU
BETTER START TALKING,

17:08.095 --> 17:10.497
OR YOU'RE BOTH
GOING DOWN,

17:10.531 --> 17:13.400
BECAUSE WE DO NOT FUCK AROUND
AT THE S. E. C.

17:14.468 --> 17:17.738
S.E.C.?
I'VE HEARD OF YOU GUYS.

17:17.771 --> 17:20.374
OH, YEAH?
I SHOULD FUCKING HOPE SO.

17:20.407 --> 17:21.909
YEAH, YOU GUYS HAVE
THOSE FEDERAL PENSION PLANS

17:21.942 --> 17:23.944
TIED IN
WITH OUR MIDDAY FUND.

17:23.977 --> 17:24.945
WHAT'S HE TALKING ABOUT?

17:24.978 --> 17:26.446
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

17:26.480 --> 17:27.447
BURNT ORANGE.

17:27.481 --> 17:30.017
I SEE NUMBERS AS COLOR.
I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.

17:30.050 --> 17:31.385
FIVE YEARS AGO,
UNCLE SAM

17:31.418 --> 17:33.954
BET YOUR RETIREMENT PLANS
ON OUR GOOD JUDGMENT.

17:33.987 --> 17:35.556
IT'S ALL RIGHT HERE
IN THE FILES.

17:35.589 --> 17:38.492
IF WE GO DOWN, YOU GO DOWN.
THAT'S RIGHT, MEATBALL.

17:38.525 --> 17:41.295
NOT ONLY ARE YOU GONNA
LET THE TWO OF US OFF
THE HOOK RIGHT HERE,

17:41.328 --> 17:43.330
BUT YOU'RE GONNA GIVE
YOUR BOSSES IN D. C. A RING

17:43.363 --> 17:46.466
TO MAKE SURE THAT OUR FIRM'S
ROAD TO SUCCESS

17:46.500 --> 17:50.604
IS PAVED WITH THE FEDS' GOOD
GRACES, PLENTY OF DEREGULATIONS,

17:50.637 --> 17:54.908
AND A LAISSEZ‐FAIRE SENSE OF
LETTING US DO OUR GODDAMN JOBS.

17:54.942 --> 17:56.376
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
AGENT SCARY LIPS?

17:56.410 --> 17:58.111
YOUR SCARY LIPS
TASTIN' MY HAIRY SHIT?

17:58.145 --> 18:00.480
YOU TASTIN' DOUG WILSON'S
WORLD‐FAMOUS BEEF STEW?

18:00.514 --> 18:03.183
HOW'S IT GOING DOWN?
IT'S KIND OF SPICY, RIGHT?

18:03.217 --> 18:04.418
WHEW.

18:04.451 --> 18:05.452
OH, SHIT.

18:05.485 --> 18:08.021
[ Chuckling ] YOU GUYS
ARE SO FUCKED RIGHT NOW.

18:08.055 --> 18:10.157
ALL I CAN THINK ABOUT
IS YOUR WIFE AND A HORSE.

18:10.190 --> 18:11.692
GO AHEAD. TAKE US DOWN.

18:11.725 --> 18:13.026
WATCH OUR SHARES PLUMMET

18:13.060 --> 18:15.429
IF YOU WANT TO RETIRE
WITH YOUR DICK IN OUR ASS,

18:15.462 --> 18:17.898
BUT IT'S A WHOLE LOT SUNNIER
IN FLORIDA.

18:17.931 --> 18:19.666
DOUG WILSON.
JESUS CHRIST.

18:19.700 --> 18:22.603
OKAY.

18:22.636 --> 18:25.305
WE'RE GONNA NEED A SECOND
TO TALK ABOUT THIS.

18:25.339 --> 18:27.374
NO WAY. I'M FREE TO GO.
SAME GOES FOR HER.

18:27.407 --> 18:30.410
AND, UM, UH,
NO HALFWAY HOUSE.

18:30.444 --> 18:31.512
NO PAROLE.

18:31.545 --> 18:32.946
NO CALLING YOUR FRIENDS
AT THE D. E. A.

18:32.980 --> 18:35.949
HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY FRIENDS
AT THE D. E. A.,

18:35.983 --> 18:37.751
DO YOU, MELNICK?

18:37.784 --> 18:38.919
DO YOU, MELNICK?

18:38.952 --> 18:42.222
NO. I DON'T HAVE
ANY FRIENDS AT THE D. E. A.

18:42.256 --> 18:45.526
AND I'M GONNA NEED THAT TAPE
BACK, FROM LAST NIGHT.

18:45.559 --> 18:46.994
THAT'S FEDERAL PROPERTY.

18:47.027 --> 18:49.296
IT'S LEVERAGE AGAINST ME,
AND I WANT IT.

18:55.035 --> 18:56.336
THAT'S IT?
THAT'S ALL OF IT?

18:56.370 --> 18:57.304
YEAH.

18:57.337 --> 19:00.307
ANY CHANCE
I COULD BUY AN EIGHTH?

19:00.340 --> 19:02.242
I'M GONNA
NEED TO SMOKE UP.

19:02.276 --> 19:03.443
YOU GOT IT.

19:03.477 --> 19:05.179
[ PLASTIC CRINKLES ]

19:05.212 --> 19:08.148
THAT'LL BE 90 BUCKS.

19:14.087 --> 19:16.056
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

19:16.089 --> 19:18.158
FUCK MY LIFE.

19:19.293 --> 19:20.928
YOU HAVE A NICE DAY, NOW.

19:20.961 --> 19:22.563
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

19:22.596 --> 19:25.299
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

19:25.332 --> 19:28.635
YOU'RE REALLY GOOD
AT BURNING SHIT DOWN.

19:28.669 --> 19:30.637
IN PRISON,
WERE YOU AND HER LIKE,

19:30.671 --> 19:31.538
"HEY.

19:31.572 --> 19:33.941
"I'M AN ARSONIST.
YOU'RE AN ARSONIST.

19:33.974 --> 19:35.976
LET'S GET TOGETHER
AND BE LESBIANS"?

19:36.009 --> 19:37.444
JUST WATCH IT BURN.

19:37.477 --> 19:41.949
GRANITE COUNTERTOPS,
DOUBLE VANITY SINKS...

19:41.982 --> 19:44.651
DON'T TALK. JUST WATCH.

19:46.653 --> 19:49.022
YOU MADE
THE RIGHT CHOICE.

19:53.093 --> 19:55.963
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

19:55.996 --> 19:58.799
NO FIRE. ZERO FIRE.
NO WAY.

19:58.832 --> 20:03.637
I‐I WORE A WIRE LAST NIGHT
FOR THE S. E. C.

20:03.670 --> 20:04.972
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

20:05.005 --> 20:06.039
THEY HAVE TAPE.

20:06.073 --> 20:08.242
THEY'LL ‐‐
THEY'LL PIN IT ON YOU.

20:08.275 --> 20:10.244
TAPE?

20:10.277 --> 20:13.413
LAST NIGHT?

20:13.447 --> 20:14.581
NO!

20:14.615 --> 20:16.216
I WAS JOKING.

20:16.250 --> 20:18.886
"I LOSE THINGS I DON'T LIKE
IN FIRE."

20:18.919 --> 20:20.988
IT'S FUNNY. YOU LAUGHED.

20:22.155 --> 20:24.291
SHIT.
THEY'LL GET ME ON ARSON.

20:24.324 --> 20:27.928
AND HE'S MISSING,
SO, ATTEMPTED MURDER, MAYBE.

20:27.961 --> 20:29.396
THEY'LL SEND ME BACK IN.

20:29.429 --> 20:30.497
MOST LIKELY.

20:30.531 --> 20:32.900
SHIT!
I GOT TO LEAVE.

20:32.933 --> 20:34.401
I GOT TO GO.

20:34.434 --> 20:37.371
ARE THERE TRAINS
STILL RUNNING?

20:37.404 --> 20:41.909
BURLINGTON VIA SPRINGFIELD.
LEAVES IN TWO HOURS.

20:41.942 --> 20:44.778
NANCITCHKA,
ALWAYS THINKING AHEAD.

20:44.811 --> 20:49.082
I'M THINKING OF US,
OF THE WEIMARANERS.

20:49.116 --> 20:50.417
COME WITH ME.

20:50.450 --> 20:53.887
YOU KNOW I CAN'T NOW,
BUT SOON.

20:53.921 --> 20:57.024
YOU'D BETTER.
I KNOW HOW YOU PUSH PEOPLE AWAY.

20:57.057 --> 20:59.026
NO, I DON'T.

20:59.059 --> 21:02.896
HMM.
IT'S SORT OF YOUR THING.

21:02.930 --> 21:04.198
DO YOU HAVE CASH?

21:04.231 --> 21:07.100
UH ‐‐ UH ‐‐
I TOOK FROM DEMETRI.

21:07.134 --> 21:09.903
NANCITCHKA,
PROMISE ME SOMETHING.

21:09.937 --> 21:11.605
ANYTHING.

21:11.638 --> 21:13.073
YOUR BROTHER‐IN‐LAW,
ANDY ‐‐

21:13.106 --> 21:14.942
HE STAYS HERE.

21:14.975 --> 21:17.978
HE NEVER COMES TO VERMONT.

21:18.011 --> 21:21.515
PROMISE.

21:21.548 --> 21:23.016
[ SIGHS ]

21:23.050 --> 21:25.219
[ MOANING ]

21:30.824 --> 21:32.459
THANK YOU.

21:32.492 --> 21:34.494
ZOYCHKA.

21:42.302 --> 21:45.439
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?
IT'S LATE.

21:45.472 --> 21:47.508
YOU GOT SOMEWHERE ELSE
YOU GOT TO BE?

21:47.541 --> 21:49.076
NO.

21:49.109 --> 21:51.645
GREAT. SIT DOWN.

21:53.280 --> 21:56.783
I THINK IT'S TIME
YOU MADE YOUR FIRST REAL ARREST.

21:56.817 --> 21:58.552
YEAH? COOL.

21:58.585 --> 21:59.486
YEAH.

21:59.520 --> 22:02.990
AND YOU KNOW
WHAT CAN GET SOMEONE ARRESTED?

22:04.057 --> 22:07.594
PIRATING SOFTWARE
CAN GET SOMEONE ARRESTED.

22:07.628 --> 22:09.696
OH. REALLY?

22:11.164 --> 22:12.266
NO.

22:12.299 --> 22:13.934
FUCK NO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:13.967 --> 22:15.969
I MEAN, HOW YOU GONNA
STEAL SOMETHING

22:16.003 --> 22:17.905
OFF A FUCKING COMPUTER,
ANYHOW, RIGHT?

22:17.938 --> 22:20.040
IT'S JUST ONES AND ZEROS.

22:20.073 --> 22:22.576
YOU CAN'T EXACTLY
WALK OFF WITH THAT SHIT.

22:22.609 --> 22:23.677
RIGHT?

22:23.710 --> 22:24.678
RIGHT.

22:24.711 --> 22:25.913
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

22:25.946 --> 22:28.015
I MEAN,
UNLESS YOU PRINT IT OUT.

22:28.048 --> 22:32.019
THEN YOU COULD
WALK OFF WITH IT.

22:32.052 --> 22:33.620
RIGHT, BOTWIN?

22:33.654 --> 22:36.123
UH‐HUH.

22:37.524 --> 22:40.360
I TRUSTED YOU.

22:45.933 --> 22:49.169
PUT THOSE ON.

22:52.439 --> 22:54.942
YOU'D GET 25% COMMISSION
ON ALL SALES,

22:54.975 --> 22:57.644
WHICH IS 15% MORE
THAN POUNCY FORKS OVER.

22:57.678 --> 23:00.981
IN ADDITION TO YOUR OLD ROUTES,
YOU'RE COVERING

23:01.014 --> 23:03.617
MORNINGSIDE HEIGHTS
WEST OF THE PARK,

23:03.650 --> 23:05.252
WHICH IS
ON ANOTHER MAP.

23:05.285 --> 23:08.956
AND THAT'S ALEX.
HE CONTROLS THE BRAIN.

23:08.989 --> 23:11.091
A CALL COMES IN,
ALEX TAKES A CODE,

23:11.124 --> 23:13.794
THE CODE GOES INTO THE BRAIN,
WHERE IT BECOMES

23:13.827 --> 23:16.763
A HUMAN, AN ADDRESS,
AND THEN A SALE.

23:16.797 --> 23:20.100
YOU GET A NEW CLIENT,
YOU GIVE IT TO ALEX,
IT GOES IN THE BRAIN.

23:20.133 --> 23:25.072
WE DO NOT DRINK LIQUIDS
NEAR THE BRAIN.

23:25.105 --> 23:26.940
ANY QUESTIONS?

23:26.974 --> 23:30.978
HOW HAVE WE
NOT MET BEFORE?

23:33.313 --> 23:36.250
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:36.283 --> 23:38.785
IT'S GOOD TO HAVE YOU HOME
AGAIN, NANCE.

23:38.819 --> 23:41.622
[ LAUGHTER IN DISTANCE ]

23:41.655 --> 23:42.990
WHAT'S GOING ON
OUT THERE?

23:43.023 --> 23:45.993
SILAS BROUGHT
A GIRL HOME.

23:46.026 --> 23:47.961
OH. IS SHE CUTE?
YEAH.

23:47.995 --> 23:50.330
WELL...

23:50.364 --> 23:51.498
GOOD FOR HIM.

23:51.532 --> 23:52.466
HE DESERVES IT.

23:52.499 --> 23:54.701
[ THE FRUIT BATS'
"SHIVERING FAWN" PLAYS ]

23:57.037 --> 23:59.239
[ LAUGHING ]

24:26.567 --> 24:28.202
GOOD MORNING, MOM.

24:29.736 --> 24:31.038
HEY.

24:31.071 --> 24:33.340
UH,
WHERE'S YOUR BROTHER?

24:33.373 --> 24:35.409
HE DIDN'T COME HOME LAST NIGHT.
HE'S NOT ANSWERING HIS PHONE.

24:37.978 --> 24:39.580
HELLO?

24:39.613 --> 24:42.282
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

24:44.351 --> 24:46.320
SILAS?

24:49.289 --> 24:51.158
SILAS!

25:39.673 --> 25:41.975
THE COMPUTER. NO.

25:42.009 --> 25:45.445
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

25:51.752 --> 25:53.453
WE SHOULD HAVE BOUGHT
THAT BEAR.

26:02.930 --> 26:06.200
